name: Erica M
text: This is the PERFECT place to go as a family to have tons of outdoor fun and to make great memories! It has so many things to do and it is incredibly clean and beautiful. They have bounce houses, a toddler playground area, mini zip line, swings and slides for kids to play on. They also have a petting farm area with a llama, sheep, pygmy goats and pot bellied pigs to feed and pet. There's a large rock climbing wall and an impressively long zip line for adults and older kids. They usually have several food trucks on site with great food and plenty of variety. There are 2 shaded pavillion areas with picnic tables to sit at and rest or enjoy something to eat. There's a small country store that sells souvenirs like t-shirts and things and often local vendors have tents set up there selling various items. The list of things to do here is truly incredible, so I'm sure there is much that I've missed. It's a very large, beautiful venue that is owned and run by some wonderful people. I HIGHLY recommend checking it out for yourself this fall! 🎃🐐🌞🍂🐑🚜❤

name: ASEmechanics West
text: We had alot of fun! It's worth the trip to see for yourself! It was a perfect day out with our family! I will definitely be back 😁 we all went on the zip line and much more!

name: Kristen Smith
text: Best pumpkin patch! 🎃

name: Kelly Fondren
text: Went here today on a field trip with my baby girl and husband.  We absolutely loved it and plan to go back soon.

name: Randie Watkins
text: We had so much fun, just wish the price was better.

name: Angel Avalos-aguilar
text: How much does the entrance cost?

name: Ryan Kirkley
text: So much to do for the price. We always have a blast!!!

name: Roxana Santander
text:
Such a great experience!!!!!!! The workers really make a difference I have the fortune to meet this awesome people that help us all day with a smile and kindness that I thanks a lot.
We went on a school trip so it was crowded but even though we could do all the activities.
A part of the traditional things (pumpkin patch, etc) the have bouncy houses , a regular slide that my kids loved , a zoo with a camel and all the other animal look pretty care , also you can make your own corn meal (bring cash 5$ per bag ) totally worth it and they offer food for lunch as well they have pretty picnic areas and we will definitely come back :)

name: Kelly Jordan
text: I like that the pumpkin is included in the price of the hayride. Lines were really long the day we went and the lady that was the cashier was less than congenial. Just a note: they used to allow you to walk to the patch if you preferred, but they no longer allow that. Also, the base price of $9.00 includes the hayride, pumpkin, and small petting zoo. Many of the other attractions are an extra fee. I would suggest wristband purchases. They have a lot of cute vignettes set up for photos.

name: Melissa Atkinson
text:
We look forward to visiting JackOlantern Lane every fall! Like that the hayride takes you to the actual pumpkin patch and you can pick your own pumpkin. There’s also a petting zoo and activities when you get off the hayride,
So it’s easy to spend quite some time there

We had our daughters birthday party there two years ago and it was such an easy process! The party room is very spacious and the employees were super helpful and accommodating.

It can get crowded but because it’s such a large place and there are so many things to do it never feels very crowded.

name: CarolAnn Miracle
text: Wonderful, fun family experience.  Best pumpkin patch around.  Don't miss it!

name: Muhammad Khan
text: Not much need more work for kids fun

name: Paul Howell
text: Made for the the end of the spectrum with very little to do for kids over the age of 5 or 6. My 6 year old was ready to go after about fifteen minutes.

text: Loved it

name: Meg Stroh
text:
Very fun experience for the family! Over priced pumpkins thad had STICKERS removed, so I assume they ran out of locally grown pumpkins and had to purchase more.
Also, admission seems over priced for an over glorified play ground and petting zoo.
But, it was a fun few hours for our kiddos.

name: randy sutton
text:
As you can see we've been coming here for a few seasons.
Always lots of fun.

name: Jabe Fincher
text: We used to take our church youth group here and they enjoyed it a lot. Nice assortment of animals and entertainment for the kids.

name: Jimmy McDade
text: My son and I had a great time here. Food is a bit high so I'd suggest eating in eufala before heading out there.

name: Julia Weaver
text: My grandchildren have enjoyed going for several years now. Very family friendly.

name: Kathy Backman
text: Spent all Day! Had a great family time.

name: kelly ellis
text: Great place, staff very friendly. Best pumpkin patch we been to so far plenty of activities for kids!

name: Ken
text:
This is a great place and my kids have plenty of time coming up with things to do while they are there. Think outside the box, enjoy the facility, pet the animals, pictures and play around. The pumpkins are costly, but hey profit has to be made to run such facilities.
I am very impressed that the owner or rep replies to the negative reviews head on and on the most professional way possible. Some people are just accustomed to butt kissing responses when they have something to complain about, it should not be that way!  🎃

resp.text: Thank you for your review. We are a family owned and operated facility and we take pride in our operation. Sometimes things are not going to be perfect no matter how hard you try and I only try to explain that in my response.

name: Megan Peters
text: Went on a field trip and had the best time. The barn area was so nice and the bounce pad area. There was a great selection of Pumpkins and the kids loved the play area with the train rides and corn boxes. The walk to the slide and zip line is a doozy but it was worth it! The kids enjoyed the inflatables and the lunch you can purchase there was really good and very efficient. Very clean facility and kind staff.

name: Tiger-Town Paving
text: Loved it perfect for the kids!

name: Marlene Hahn
text: We had a great time there.  There are so many activities. We had missed the wagons going to the pumpkin patch and they graciously arranged for us to have a ride there. A very nice man who I'm not sure of his name, Skipbo, ( that's probably not right) gave usxa ride to and from the pumpkin patch.

name: Danielle Wilstead
text: Me and my kids had an amazing time here! I came with my 3 boys and they gave us a ride back to our car so we didn't have to walk. It was a blast with so much to do and so helpful! We'll definitely be back!

name: Julie Barbaree
text: What sets this pumpkin patch apart is the helpfulness of the staff, the organization, and the layout of the entire facility. A lot of pumpkin patches have everything centered around one open area so that everyone is bumping into everyone trying to go from one attraction to another. Not so at Paradise Pumpkin Path, everything is spread out so that there is room to move about without stepping on someone going from one attraction to another. So much for the kids to do. I would say one of the BEST pumpkin patches around.

name: Chelsea Coleman
text: All of the activities and animals are great. But, I came to pick a pumpkin from their actual patch. When my husband, two year old and I went out there it was a squash patch with pre bought pumpkins from Walmart. The pumpkins had STICKERS on them! Then the place even had the guts to charge FIFTEEN DOLLARS per pumpkin. I CAN SAY WITH CERTAINTY THAT I WILL NOT EVER COME BACK.

resp.text: I am sorry you were disappointed but pumpkins do not grow in the south due to the hot humid weather. Information about this fact can easily be googled. They were not Walmart pumpkins I actually went to Atlanta Farmers market because they have better pumpkins. If you didn't like the pumpkins you don't have to buy them. They are also different sizes and prices on pumpkins they are not all $15. I hope you enjoyed the other 25 different events.

name: Yolanda Coleman
text: We went on our 1st grade girls trip to Paradise Pumpkin Patch. It was awesome!!  Loads of fun for the kids and super friendly staff!!!!

name: Shawn Fowler
text: Lots of fun for the family.  We have made the hour drive from Columbus,  GA every year with our kids.  Each year it gets even better. Highly recommend.

name: Cassandra Neal
text: My family and I have been to this pumpkin patch 2 years in a row. There is a horse there named "Jake" and he bit my son on the front of his chest when he was standing for me to take a picture. I told a worker there and she said that horse just bit someone else recently. This was very traumatic for my son..he is 10 and has autism. Our trip was ruined and we just paid to get in, with no military discount. Otherwise, this farm was nice. Just advise to stay away from this horse.

resp.text: I have had that horse for 30 years. He is like family. I wasn't there but I have never seen or heard of that horse biting anyone. I also have an autistic child and he rode that horse in horse shows all over Alabama. I have used him in the pony rides before he got so old. I have not had any of my workers tell me that horse bit anyone. If I thought any of our animals were dangerous I would not have them where children could get near them. I apologize if you had a bad experience with the horse there is a possibility he had feed on his clothes. When you are around animals anything can happen and I understand that is a liability of having animals. I don't think this justifies a 2 star rating. I have not increased our admission fee in 7 years. At this point the only way I can give a military discount is to go up on the admission price. I appreciate all the men and women that serve our country. I think our admission fee is very reasonable for what we offer. You obviously did or you would not have returned the 2nd year.

name: Daniela Collier
text: The place sounds a lot better on paper than it actually is. Kids may have a decent time but it is not nearly as fun and exciting as they make it seem. My kids were bored and filthy after 15 minutes and I felt disappointed the moment we got there.  Staff is also combative as you can see for yourself in a response that they posted on here in reference to another customers concerns. I'd save the trip and find a nicer location. Lane Southern Orchard is nice as long as you go early in the season for the corn maze. They have a very nice playground and offer military discount. Plus you can buy wine so bonus!

resp.text: I am sorry you did not have a good time. I try to be open minded to every review I receive, regardless if it is 1 star or 5 star. There is always ways to improve your business if you will listen to your customers. But I also do not understand how your children got bored and nasty 15 minutes after you arrived. If they were bored how did they get nasty. We keep our facility very clean and the first 15 minutes would not get you through the petting zoo. Is this a negative review on our Pumpkin Patch or are you trying to advertise another pumpkin patch at my expense. I am not trying to be combative but we do not sell alcoholic beverages at our pumpkin patch so bonus! It is unfortunate that  you have nothing better to do than write a negative review about our facility on Christmas eve 2 months after we closed our pumpkin patch for the season. Merry Christmas
